3. Current Blocking Issue

Error

youtube_transcript_api._errors.TranscriptsDisabled:
Could not retrieve a transcript for the video ...
Subtitles are disabled for this video

Then wrapped as:

RuntimeError: Transcripts disabled for video popvxbg9Flc
Process completed with exit code 1.

Where It Happens

Inside:

transcript_list = YouTubeTranscriptApi.list_transcripts(video_id)

And specifically:

except TranscriptsDisabled as e:
    raise RuntimeError(f"Transcripts disabled for video {video_id}") from e

This hard-fails the pipeline.

⸻

4. Important Context
	•	The user explicitly states Subtitles are enabled on both videos (so the error is a false negative.
	•	This is running in GitHub Actions (headless environment).
	•	youtube-transcript-api is being used.

⸻

5. Likely Root Cause

This is a known issue with youtube-transcript-api in CI/headless environments:
	•	YouTube blocks requests based on:
	  •	IP reputation
	  •	Missing cookies
  	•	No user agent
  	•	Data center IPs
  	•	The library interprets blocked responses as TranscriptsDisabled.

This is not actually “subtitles disabled”.
It is YouTube blocking transcript extraction.

⸻

6. Current Script Behavior

Transcript Flow

try:
    transcript_list = YouTubeTranscriptApi.list_transcripts(video_id)
except TranscriptsDisabled:
    raise RuntimeError(...)

Then:
	1.	Try manually created transcripts
	2.	Try auto-generated transcripts
	3.	Try fallback transcript
	4.	If nothing → raise RuntimeError

Critical Flaw

The script treats TranscriptsDisabled as a fatal condition instead of:
	•	Retrying
	•	Using alternative fetch methods
	•	Falling back to HTML caption extraction
	•	Logging and skipping
	•	Continuing other URLs

This causes the entire Action to fail.

⸻

7. What Needs To Be Fixed

A. Do NOT hard fail on TranscriptsDisabled

Replace:

except TranscriptsDisabled as e:
    raise RuntimeError(...)

With something like:
	•	Retry with backoff
	•	Attempt direct transcript fetch
	•	Attempt get_transcript() instead of list_transcripts()
	•	Or gracefully skip with warning

⸻

B. Improve Robustness for CI Environments

Potential solutions:

Option 1 – Use get_transcript() directly

YouTubeTranscriptApi.get_transcript(video_id, languages=preferred_langs)

This sometimes works when list_transcripts() fails.

⸻

Option 2 – Add custom request headers / user agent
The library uses requests internally. In CI environments, YouTube may block default headers.

A proper fix might involve:
	•	Monkey-patching HTTP client
	•	Supplying custom requests.Session with headers

⸻

Option 3 – Add retry logic
Wrap transcript fetch in retry with exponential backoff:
	•	3 attempts
	•	sleep 2s, 5s, 10s

⸻

Option 4 – Soft-fail per video
Instead of:

raise RuntimeError

Do:

print warning
return ""

And allow other videos to continue.

⸻

